1
00:00:38,420 --> 00:00:41,060
=How to Train Your Killer=

2
00:00:41,060 --> 00:00:43,900
=Episode 24=

3
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:46,720
Come out.

4
00:00:49,390 --> 00:00:50,230
Let's go.

5
00:00:55,150 --> 00:00:56,430
Sharp, aren't you?

6
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,180
If you know what's best for you,

7
00:00:58,470 --> 00:00:59,710
hand over the treasures

8
00:00:59,710 --> 00:01:00,840
you're carrying.

9
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:02,920
I'll spare your life.

10
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,120
You're nothing but ants
from the Sky Pavilion,

11
00:01:06,870 --> 00:01:08,640
so why bother hiding?

12
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,400
What nonsense are you spouting?

13
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,920
Master of the Sky Pavilion,

14
00:01:14,790 --> 00:01:17,680
are you certain you want them
sent to their doom?

15
00:01:27,070 --> 00:01:28,590
You actually guessed it.

16
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:36,710
Master, are you planning to rob me?

17
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,400
Don't put it so harshly.

18
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,000
I'm just curious

19
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,840
about what is so special
about that stone

20
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:45,150
that made you spend 50,000 taels
to buy it.

21
00:01:45,790 --> 00:01:47,070
No comment.

22
00:01:47,590 --> 00:01:48,710
Then I'll have to ask you

23
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:50,310
to visit our pavilion.

24
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,000
I didn't expect it to be Wu Yun.

25
00:02:58,840 --> 00:02:59,710
What should we do now?

26
00:02:59,710 --> 00:03:01,360
What else can we do?
We can't defeat him.

27
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:02,840
Well,

28
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,800
who exactly is this Wu Yun?

29
00:03:05,330 --> 00:03:06,630
Why does he want that stone?

30
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,840
What's going on?

31
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:09,280
Let's go.

32
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:10,950
We'll deal
with tomorrow's matters first.

33
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,680
Go, go, hurry!

34
00:03:14,170 --> 00:03:15,280
We're leaving, come on!

35
00:03:15,810 --> 00:03:17,240
Hey, we're just letting this go?

36
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,880
All that effort for nothing.

37
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:21,030
Let's at least grab a late-night meal.

38
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:21,970
Hey, you rascal Shiyi!

39
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,090
- Lord Zhao.
- Prime Minister Gu.

40
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:31,580
(Prime Minister's Residence)
Lord Gu.

41
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:32,430
Please, come inside.

42
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:33,960
- Prime Minister Gu!
- My Lord.

43
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,240
Congratulations.

44
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:37,240
Congratulations.

45
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,450
- I wish you longevity and grace,
- Congratulations.

46
00:03:39,630 --> 00:03:41,120
and enjoy endless blessings.

47
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,590
- Welcome.
- Please, this way.

48
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:44,710
A small gift.

49
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:45,750
Everyone's already inside.

50
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:46,680
Please.

51
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,430
All is well.

52
00:03:48,430 --> 00:03:49,280
Lord Peng.

53
00:03:49,290 --> 00:03:50,310
You're thoughtful.

54
00:03:56,430 --> 00:03:57,840
Your Highness, your presence

55
00:03:57,840 --> 00:04:00,560
truly brings glory
to this humble courtyard.

56
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:02,400
Father-in-law, you're too polite.

57
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:08,310
Didn't Qingyao come with you?

58
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:11,190
Qingyao wished to prepare
your gift personally.

59
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:12,360
She's been slightly delayed.

60
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,260
She'll arrive shortly.

61
00:04:13,430 --> 00:04:14,270
Alright.

62
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:16,140
Please, come inside.

63
00:04:16,150 --> 00:04:17,000
Alright.

64
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:26,240
In a while, give him this painting.

65
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,260
Take him to the crabapple tree
in the backyard.

66
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,600
Talk more about my mother.

67
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,200
I believe,

68
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:35,240
my father might change his mind.

69
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,390
You stayed up all night

70
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,560
just to sew this?

71
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,790
Remember to make it look convincing.

72
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:49,800
He never responds well to force.

73
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:52,070
As long as I act a little coy,

74
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,120
he'll give in to whatever I want.

75
00:04:58,720 --> 00:04:59,630
All these years,

76
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,750
I've never seen the Master

77
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,920
change his decision

78
00:05:06,190 --> 00:05:07,120
once it's made.

79
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,360
At this point,

80
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:15,480
we can only do our best

81
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,050
and leave the rest to fate.

82
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,640
Shiyi.

83
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:26,270
What's wrong?

84
00:05:26,950 --> 00:05:28,460
Why is your forehead covered in sweat?

85
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,840
I…

86
00:05:32,490 --> 00:05:33,800
I've never been this close to him.

87
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,600
I feel uneasy inside.

88
00:05:37,630 --> 00:05:38,830
What if I mess it up?

89
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:45,110
Don't be afraid.

90
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,760
Look at me.

91
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:50,310
When you get there later,

92
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,100
just call him father straight away.

93
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,920
Make your voice soft.

94
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:55,190
Lower your posture a bit.

95
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:57,630
Then give his sleeve a gentle tug.

96
00:05:58,620 --> 00:05:59,600
Whenever I act sweet,

97
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:02,240
he always falls for it.

98
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,440
Shiyi,

99
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,390
you're all I have now.

100
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,840
We're here.

101
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:34,760
Let's go.

102
00:06:51,660 --> 00:06:54,420
(Prime Minister's Residence)

103
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,600
How is His Majesty's health?

104
00:07:08,050 --> 00:07:09,190
Not very well at the moment.

105
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,850
- My lady.
- Why hasn't Qingyao arrived yet?

106
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:15,760
Yao, you are here.

107
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:16,790
Father.

108
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:23,040
Why are you acting shy

109
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:25,750
with the Crown Prince around?

110
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,750
Perhaps it's been too long
since our last meeting.

111
00:07:29,340 --> 00:07:31,250
I have missed you dearly.

112
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,950
Oh, my dear daughter.

113
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,160
Ever since you got married,

114
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:41,560
you've grown distant from me.

115
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:43,760
Father,

116
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:46,160
I

117
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,000
have something to discuss
with you privately.

118
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:51,670
Oh.

119
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,870
What is it

120
00:07:53,870 --> 00:07:55,830
that cannot be said
in front of His Highness?

121
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:01,350
It's all right.

122
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:02,750
Please go ahead.

123
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:06,190
Please be more understanding.

124
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,830
Father, let's go.

125
00:08:21,830 --> 00:08:22,670
OK.

126
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,320
Yao,

127
00:08:41,910 --> 00:08:43,960
you brought me here on purpose,

128
00:08:44,150 --> 00:08:46,150
what is it you want to tell me?

129
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:51,440
This is a birthday gift for you.

130
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:53,480
Let me see what my sweet daughter

131
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,240
has prepared for me this time.

132
00:09:15,390 --> 00:09:16,230
Yao,

133
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:19,630
I truly love

134
00:09:20,730 --> 00:09:21,900
this birthday gift.

135
00:09:22,620 --> 00:09:23,490
Do you think

136
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:26,840
if your mother were still alive,

137
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:30,180
would she be pleased
with my current state?

138
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,840
Of course she would.

139
00:09:33,150 --> 00:09:35,240
Seeing you now as the Crown Princess,

140
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,750
she would surely be filled with joy.

141
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:39,260
But, father,

142
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:42,060
you seem you're not pleased with me.

143
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,340
Yao,

144
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:47,980
why would you think that?

145
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:50,300
Father,

146
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:51,980
if...

147
00:09:54,380 --> 00:09:55,660
I mean, if

148
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:58,660
I hadn't married the Crown Prince,

149
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:01,300
and Mother were still alive,

150
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,940
and our family lived far away
from the capital

151
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:07,300
as ordinary folk,

152
00:10:08,460 --> 00:10:09,420
would you be willing?

153
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:14,580
In this world,

154
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:17,220
there aren't so many 'ifs'.

155
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:19,420
Life in this world

156
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:22,100
has many moments

157
00:10:22,620 --> 00:10:23,700
that don't go as one wishes.

158
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:25,420
But I want to know,

159
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:27,700
in your heart,

160
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:30,180
between being the Prime Minister
and family,

161
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:32,180
which one matters more?

162
00:10:35,540 --> 00:10:37,060
Father, can't you make a choice?

163
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:41,700
This question holds no meaning.

164
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:44,940
If I were but a common man,

165
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:47,340
I'd have no means to protect you,

166
00:10:47,660 --> 00:10:48,700
nor your mother.

167
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:50,020
Why can't you?

168
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:52,340
Even as ordinary folk,

169
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:53,290
if we live with effort,

170
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:54,180
and stay content,

171
00:10:54,180 --> 00:10:55,660
we can still spend our lives in peace.

172
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:57,300
You don't understand.

173
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,300
In times of chaos,

174
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:01,100
common folk are like tiny ants,

175
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,780
their fate is decided

176
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:04,500
by others.

177
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:05,660
Ants may be small,

178
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:07,220
but chaos will be stilled one day.

179
00:11:07,220 --> 00:11:09,180
Yet once life is lost, it cannot return.

180
00:11:16,820 --> 00:11:17,660
I'm sorry.

181
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,140
Yao,

182
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:22,980
I lied to you.

183
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:26,860
Your mother

184
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,700
did not die from difficult birth

185
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,020
while giving birth to you at all.

186
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:32,540
Instead,

187
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:35,220
after giving birth to you,

188
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,860
she was harmed by a wicked man.

189
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:41,940
Who was that person?

190
00:11:41,940 --> 00:11:43,020
He is someone

191
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,420
to whom I would bow my head

192
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:47,020
even if I were the Prime Minister.

193
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:02,350
♪When a breeze passes by♪

194
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:06,190
♪The sand and wind burn with longing♪

195
00:12:06,190 --> 00:12:08,830
♪Fearless even when thirst
goes unquenched♪

196
00:12:09,150 --> 00:12:12,310
♪Like a camel wandering
with eyes closed♪

197
00:12:12,670 --> 00:12:15,630
♪When the rain quietly settles♪

198
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:18,950
♪I think of our sorrow yet unknown♪

199
00:12:19,150 --> 00:12:21,870
♪No need to hum the song of the wind♪

200
00:12:22,030 --> 00:12:25,670
♪Ignoring the sky darkening before us♪

201
00:12:25,830 --> 00:12:27,430
♪I finally understood that truth♪

202
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:28,910
♪Yet you have already faded away♪

203
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:30,750
♪I lose my way in the night♪

204
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,230
♪Not knowing how to still my heart♪

205
00:12:32,230 --> 00:12:33,910
♪Loving you feels like lifetimes apart♪

206
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:36,870
♪Yet longing flows back into verse♪

207
00:12:37,310 --> 00:12:39,750
♪For you and me to meet again♪

208
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:43,030
♪We must cross a thousand years
of promises♪

209
00:12:43,310 --> 00:12:45,390
♪In the pouring rain♪

210
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:49,750
♪As if you are still by my side♪
